                Universal Screenshot Input
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-cyan-100/70">
                Works with any creative tool via screenshot mode. Capture from
                Photoshop, Procreate, or any app you love.
              </p>
              <div
                class="absolute transition-opacity opacity-0 top-4 right-4 group-hover:opacity-100"
              >
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-purple-300 rounded bg-purple-500/20"
                  >Workflow</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>

            <div
              class="relative p-8 transition-all duration-300 border rounded-2xl bg-base-300/40 backdrop-blur-sm border-white/5 hover:border-white/20 hover:shadow-xl hover:bg-base-300/60 group"
            >
              <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-purple-500/20">
                  <svg
                    class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-400"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M4 7v10c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4V7M4 7c0 2.21 3.582 4 8 4s8-1.79 8-4M4 7c0-2.21 3.582-4 8-4s8 1.79 8 4m0 5c0 2.21-3.582 4-8 4s-8-1.79-8-4"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </div>
              <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-bold text-white">
                Stable Diffusion Universe
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-cyan-100/70">
                Access the entire ecosystem of Stable Diffusion models, LoRAs,
                and embeddings from the community.
              </p>
              <div
                class="absolute transition-opacity opacity-0 top-4 right-4 group-hover:opacity-100"
              >
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-purple-300 rounded bg-purple-500/20"
                  >Models</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>

            <div
              class="relative p-8 transition-all duration-300 border rounded-2xl bg-base-300/40 backdrop-blur-sm border-white/5 hover:border-white/20 hover:shadow-xl hover:bg-base-300/60 group"
            >
              <div class="flex items-start mb-4">
                <div class="p-3 rounded-lg bg-purple-500/20">
                  <svg
                    class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-400"
                    fill="none"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M19 11H5m14 0a2 2 0 012 2v6a2 2 0 01-2 2H5a2 2 0 01-2-2v-6a2 2 0 012-2m14 0V9a2 2 0 00-2-2M5 11V9a2 2 0 012-2m0 0V5a2 2 0 012-2h6a2 2 0 012 2v2M7 7h10"
                    ></path>
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-1 ml-auto text-xs font-bold text-white rounded bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-pink-500"
                  >PRO</span
                >
              </div>
              <h3 class="mb-3 text-xl font-bold text-white">
                Preset Banks & Groups
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-cyan-100/70">
                Save your perfect settings as presets in organized groups.
                Switch between looks instantly and iterate with confidence.
              </p>
              <div
                class="absolute transition-opacity opacity-0 top-4 right-4 group-hover:opacity-100"
              >
                <span
                  class="px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-purple-300 rounded bg-purple-500/20"
                  >Workflow</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
